The paper discusses the design of codebooks for analog beamforming in millimeter wave communication, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), and signal processing (cs.SY). The use of millimeter wave communication also suggests a potential connection to the sub-category of computer science focused on millimeter wave technology (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of analog beamforming, which could fall under the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
